 with correlations nearing 0.75 at full marker density.
 In contrast,
 secondary traits—
such as secondary tuber flesh or sprout color—
showed lower predictive values,
 even with more markers.
 This variability reflects differences in genetic architecture,
 with some traits likely controlled by major loci,
 and others influenced by more polygenic and complex effects.
\end_layout

